WEBVTT

00:04.134 --> 00:04.352
.

00:04.395 --> 00:07.137
- Previously
on "Midnight, Texas"...

00:07.181 --> 00:08.530
- I went to see Kai
last night.

00:08.573 --> 00:10.184
- You're human.
- Let's just say

00:10.227 --> 00:11.750
demons took a lot from me,

00:11.794 --> 00:14.710
and I've dedicated my life
to settling the score.

00:14.753 --> 00:16.668
- I wouldn't mind having
the demon ripped out of me.

00:16.712 --> 00:18.322
- I love you
just the way you are.

00:18.366 --> 00:20.498
- I'm Celeste.
- You're a Dark Witch.

00:20.542 --> 00:23.066
- Either let the curse
run its course, or--

00:23.110 --> 00:25.503
- Embrace the darkness.
- I have to leave Midnight,

00:25.547 --> 00:28.158
and I have to do it alone.
- But I love you.

00:28.202 --> 00:29.681
- Kai and I have been together
for a long time,

00:29.725 --> 00:33.076
but that does not mean
that I want this to end.

00:33.120 --> 00:35.165
- I found this in Lyric's room.
- She's gone.

00:35.209 --> 00:37.211
- It's monster energy.

00:42.607 --> 00:45.088
- Whatever it is,
you can tell me.

00:45.132 --> 00:46.655
[tense music]

00:46.698 --> 00:49.527
- I know Kai is stockpiling
supernatural powers.

00:49.571 --> 00:51.268
I saw them.
- No.

00:51.312 --> 00:54.402
He locks them away
for safekeeping.

00:54.445 --> 00:58.362
The energy that he extracts,
it's like toxic waste.

00:58.406 --> 01:00.799
Once he removes it,
he can't just throw it away.

01:00.843 --> 01:03.411
It's dangerous.
- And you know that?

01:03.454 --> 01:05.326
Or is that what he told you?

01:05.369 --> 01:07.371
- [scoffs]

01:07.415 --> 01:09.634
- He could be playing you.
- No, I have been sleeping

01:09.678 --> 01:12.463
next to the man for 12 years.
He can't play me.

01:12.507 --> 01:16.119
- Lyric told me she killed
Sequoia to protect Kai.

01:16.163 --> 01:18.556
And all the visions
Sequoia showed me

01:18.600 --> 01:20.602
pointed a finger
at Kai keeping vials.

01:20.645 --> 01:24.345
If they're just waste--
- Manfred, I know Kai.

01:24.388 --> 01:27.522
He would never
put anyone in danger.

01:27.565 --> 01:30.438
You need to trust me.

01:30.481 --> 01:32.135
Do you trust me?

01:32.179 --> 01:35.138
[tense music]

01:35.182 --> 01:40.317
♪

01:40.361 --> 01:43.451
- Creek, you're here.

01:43.494 --> 01:47.281
- I can come back, I--
- No, no.

01:49.370 --> 01:51.372
Come in.

01:51.415 --> 01:53.678
- Hi, Creek, um...

01:53.722 --> 01:57.247
I will let you two catch up.

01:59.815 --> 02:01.599
- I'm so sorry.

02:05.560 --> 02:07.431
What--what are you doing here?

02:07.475 --> 02:09.259
- What am I--

02:09.303 --> 02:11.435
Your voicemail said that
it was an emergency.

02:11.479 --> 02:13.611
- What?
- I kept trying to call,

02:13.655 --> 02:15.265
but couldn't get through.
I was so worried.

02:15.309 --> 02:18.747
- What--what voicemail?
I didn't call.

02:18.790 --> 02:21.837
[phone beeps]

02:21.880 --> 02:24.927
Creek, please come home.

02:24.970 --> 02:27.538
I need you.
It's an emergency.

02:29.540 --> 02:32.195
- What, what is that face?

02:32.239 --> 02:34.197
- That wasn't me.

02:34.241 --> 02:37.200
[dramatic music]

02:37.244 --> 02:40.943
♪

02:40.986 --> 02:42.814
Who would mess with us
like this?

02:42.858 --> 02:45.208
- Manfred, I've had
weak moments too, okay?

02:45.252 --> 02:46.731
You don't have to cover.

02:46.775 --> 02:48.298
- What am I covering for?

02:48.342 --> 02:52.215
[phone buzzes]

02:52.259 --> 02:55.479
Damn, I was supposed to meet up
with Lem and Olivia.

02:55.523 --> 02:58.743
- Oh, but, I--never mind.

02:58.787 --> 03:00.832
I should just grab
the rest of my stuff

03:00.876 --> 03:04.532
and head back, anyway.
- No, no, no.

03:04.575 --> 03:07.665
They miss you, Lem and Olivia,
they miss you.

03:07.709 --> 03:09.972
You should come with me
to Home Cookin'.

03:10.015 --> 03:15.282
- Well, I've missed them too,
a lot.

03:17.675 --> 03:19.677
- Shall we?

03:24.378 --> 03:25.640
- Hey!
- Oh!

03:25.683 --> 03:27.511
[both laugh]

03:27.555 --> 03:31.254
- What you got there?
- It's from Celeste.

03:31.298 --> 03:34.344
The butterfly
signifies metamorphosis.

03:34.388 --> 03:38.566
That'll be me tonight,
spreading my wings.

03:38.609 --> 03:40.655
- What's in it?

03:40.698 --> 03:43.658
[tense music]

03:43.701 --> 03:45.486
♪

03:45.529 --> 03:48.271
- Everything I need
to pledge my loyalty

03:48.315 --> 03:50.317
to the Children of Theophilus.

03:50.360 --> 03:51.709
It's a ritual in a box.

03:51.753 --> 03:53.668
Kind of neat, right?

03:53.711 --> 03:55.670
- Yeah, what's a butterfly
need with a knife?

03:55.713 --> 03:57.280
[chuckles]

03:57.324 --> 03:58.716
I'm not so sure
about this, Feej.

03:58.760 --> 04:01.545
Dark Magic
always has a price.

04:03.504 --> 04:08.552
- Losing you is worse
than any price I could pay.

04:08.596 --> 04:10.641
The pledge is the only thing

04:10.685 --> 04:12.774
that keeps the curse
from killing you.

04:14.993 --> 04:17.387
- You know, I hate that you
have to do this for me.

04:17.431 --> 04:19.607
- It's for us.

04:19.650 --> 04:24.742
I am a little scared,
but I'm also kind of excited.

04:24.786 --> 04:27.571
What if the idea
of a Dark Witch was perpetuated

04:27.615 --> 04:31.358
to keep some of us from
realizing our full potential?

04:31.401 --> 04:34.883
I'm light and dark.

04:37.625 --> 04:40.410
It's time I accept
all of myself.

04:42.499 --> 04:44.327
- Then I will too.

04:45.850 --> 04:47.635
- Thank you.

04:47.678 --> 04:52.509
- Monte Cristo, who knew?
It's lunch and dessert!

04:52.553 --> 04:54.468
[upbeat rock music]

04:54.511 --> 04:57.601
- It's good to have you back.
- It's good to be back.

04:57.645 --> 05:00.517
- Mm, sorry, you were saying
about Patience.

05:02.389 --> 05:04.391
- I think Kai sold her
a bill of goods,

05:04.434 --> 05:06.741
that he's keeping
the monster powers contained

05:06.784 --> 05:10.397
because they're toxic, but I
know they can be recycled.

05:10.440 --> 05:12.703
I found this in Lyric's room.

05:12.747 --> 05:15.706
[tense music]

05:15.750 --> 05:17.360
♪

05:17.404 --> 05:19.536
It contained something
that made her invisible.

05:19.580 --> 05:22.757
She cloaked herself with it
before she killed Sequoia

05:22.800 --> 05:25.803
to protect Kai.
- To protect Kai from what?

05:25.847 --> 05:27.588
- Sequoia's visions
were all about

05:27.631 --> 05:29.633
getting me to the vials.
They're Kai's secret.

05:29.677 --> 05:30.982
The powers can be weaponized,

05:31.026 --> 05:33.768
and he's lying about it
to his wife.

05:33.811 --> 05:36.640
- What makes you think Patience
isn't lying to you?

05:36.684 --> 05:39.643
- Fiji performed an intention
spell on Patience.

05:39.687 --> 05:41.819
Her intentions are pure.

05:41.863 --> 05:45.345
She believes Kai's whole
righteous healer act.

05:45.388 --> 05:47.477
Meanwhile, he adds
to his arsenal

05:47.521 --> 05:50.524
and he disarms the most
powerful players in Midnight.

05:50.567 --> 05:52.134
- I can't argue with that.
- Yes.

05:52.177 --> 05:54.745
But "disarm" is a bit strong.

05:54.789 --> 05:57.879
I went to Kai voluntarily.
So did Rev.

05:57.922 --> 05:59.576
He cured your demon cancer.

05:59.620 --> 06:01.839
Kai's been nothing
but an asset to Midnight.

06:01.883 --> 06:04.712
- Well, if he's such an asset,

06:04.755 --> 06:07.758
I say we put him to the test.

06:07.802 --> 06:10.500
What if Lem goes and asks
for his powers back?

06:10.544 --> 06:14.112
If Kai has no ulterior motive,
he'll give them back.

06:14.156 --> 06:17.377
If he's hiding something,
he won't.

06:22.033 --> 06:23.818
- I'm ready.

06:30.085 --> 06:31.956
Baby, your hands are giving
me flashbacks

06:32.000 --> 06:33.828
to the Middle Ages.

06:33.871 --> 06:35.525
That bar must be rowdy.

06:41.139 --> 06:43.620
What's wrong?

06:43.664 --> 06:45.056
What is it?

06:45.100 --> 06:47.668
- I'm hiding something
from you.

06:49.757 --> 06:52.542
A few weeks ago,
I got jumped outside the bar

06:52.586 --> 06:55.458
by some demons,
and I fought back.

06:55.502 --> 06:58.113
At first, it was self-defense,
but I wanted more.

06:58.156 --> 07:00.898
[dramatic music]

07:00.942 --> 07:02.987
I'm demon-hunting again.

07:03.031 --> 07:08.689
♪

07:08.732 --> 07:11.039
- Is that it?

07:11.082 --> 07:13.041
You scared me.

07:13.084 --> 07:15.086
- You're not mad?

07:15.130 --> 07:16.871
- Baby, this is what
you were made for.

07:16.914 --> 07:19.090
I'm not mad; I'm proud.

07:19.134 --> 07:21.441
- You've had a change of heart.

07:21.484 --> 07:23.617
- Well, maybe I'm older
and wiser.

07:25.793 --> 07:27.925
- Thank you.

07:27.969 --> 07:29.492
It feels good.

07:29.536 --> 07:31.625
I feel like
I've found my place again.

07:31.668 --> 07:33.017
I was just worried
you'd be upset.

07:33.061 --> 07:35.759
- I fight my demon half
every day.

07:35.803 --> 07:37.892
You aren't doing
anything wrong.

07:40.764 --> 07:44.202
- Human or vampire.

07:44.246 --> 07:46.596
[light music]

07:46.640 --> 07:49.643
It's for you to decide.

07:49.686 --> 07:51.122
- Not anymore.

07:51.166 --> 07:54.604
I made this decision
without you last time.

07:54.648 --> 07:56.127
Never again.

07:56.171 --> 07:58.695
- [laughs]

07:58.739 --> 08:02.873
I know I gave you a hard time
about becoming human.

08:02.917 --> 08:05.267
♪

08:05.310 --> 08:08.575
But after my dad's,
I don't care.

08:08.618 --> 08:13.014
Whatever form you take,
you'll still be you,

08:13.057 --> 08:17.975
and that is the only good thing
in the world that I am sure of.

08:18.019 --> 08:22.545
- At your father's,
when you were under his spell,

08:22.589 --> 08:25.853
I never felt so helpless.

08:25.896 --> 08:28.595
I do want my powers back.

08:28.638 --> 08:31.815
Right or wrong, it's who I am,

08:31.859 --> 08:37.212
but children won't be possible
as a vampire.

08:38.605 --> 08:39.954
That door closes.

08:39.997 --> 08:43.653
- Well.

08:43.697 --> 08:50.181
If we want a family someday,
then we'll foster or adopt.

08:50.225 --> 08:52.836
There are kids with no one.

08:52.880 --> 08:55.317
I used to be one.

08:55.360 --> 08:58.015
- Are you saying
that you're willing

08:58.059 --> 09:00.714
to be married
to a vampire again?

09:02.367 --> 09:07.677
- If that vampire is you, yes.

09:10.767 --> 09:12.726
[knock at door]

09:19.776 --> 09:22.692
- Another Frito-pie pizza
for you, Mr. Bridger.

09:22.736 --> 09:24.041
- Thank you.

09:24.085 --> 09:25.956
- So are you on that
all-pizza diet?

09:26.000 --> 09:27.697
- [laughs]

09:27.741 --> 09:29.307
- Thank you.

09:31.266 --> 09:34.225
[both grunt]

09:34.269 --> 09:37.011
[slow rock music]

09:37.054 --> 09:39.753
- Care to partake
in my last meal?

09:42.103 --> 09:45.106
- Oh, I brought you some food.

09:46.977 --> 09:48.936
What was left.

09:51.678 --> 09:53.680
Kai, what's wrong?

09:59.163 --> 10:02.123
[dramatic musical flourish]

10:02.166 --> 10:04.081
- You're sleeping with him.

10:04.125 --> 10:07.171
- I--I don't know
what you're talking about.

10:07.215 --> 10:09.173
[tense music]

10:09.217 --> 10:11.045
♪

10:11.088 --> 10:13.090
Manfred, it's me.

10:13.134 --> 10:14.309
I miss you today, darling.

10:14.352 --> 10:17.268
I miss your smell.

10:17.312 --> 10:19.270
- You thought you were calling
Manfred, but you called me.

10:19.314 --> 10:22.752
- That's not me.

10:22.796 --> 10:24.188
That's not me!

10:27.670 --> 10:27.844
.

10:27.888 --> 10:30.673
- I didn't leave that message!
- Oh, you didn't

10:30.717 --> 10:32.153
leave that message.
What do you take me for?

10:32.196 --> 10:33.154
You think I don't
see you two together

10:33.197 --> 10:34.546
all the time, flirting?

10:34.590 --> 10:35.809
- Oh, I'm not allowed
to have a friend?

10:35.852 --> 10:37.332
You--you have
a lot of friends.

10:37.375 --> 10:39.073
- Friends?
- Yeah, yes.

10:39.116 --> 10:41.292
You think it makes me
feel good, sitting at home,

10:41.336 --> 10:44.165
while you're off in Tulum
with your holistic harem?

10:44.208 --> 10:46.297
- What are you talking about?
Those trips were helping

10:46.341 --> 10:48.212
to build our future.
They were for us!

10:48.256 --> 10:49.823
- For us?

10:49.866 --> 10:51.346
- Here, here,
come look at this.

10:51.389 --> 10:53.261
There is no
outgoing call to you.

10:53.304 --> 10:54.828
- Yeah, a call log
can be edited.

10:54.871 --> 10:57.482
And if you can't admit guilt,
please just drop it.

10:57.526 --> 10:59.354
- You really think
I'd do this?

10:59.397 --> 11:00.790
- I don't know
what you would do anymore.

11:00.834 --> 11:04.054
- What is that
supposed to mean?

11:04.098 --> 11:05.665
- You're sleeping
with a married woman,

11:05.708 --> 11:08.450
and we broke up, like,
five minutes ago.

11:08.493 --> 11:10.713
I guess I just didn't think
you were that guy.

11:10.757 --> 11:12.715
- I'm not that guy.

11:12.759 --> 11:15.457
You just--you left,

11:15.500 --> 11:18.721
and I made some
out-of-character choices.

11:18.765 --> 11:22.159
- I don't get why you can't
just own up to it.

11:22.203 --> 11:24.379
You tied one on last night,
left me a voicemail,

11:24.422 --> 11:26.250
and when I showed up,
you regretted it.

11:26.294 --> 11:27.687
- No, I would never do that.

11:27.730 --> 11:30.167
I care way too much
about you.

11:30.211 --> 11:32.169
- Do you care about Patience?

11:32.213 --> 11:35.172
[tense music]

11:35.216 --> 11:38.480
- Listen, I really wasn't
doing well after us.

11:38.523 --> 11:42.397
And--and Patience
was there for me.

11:42.440 --> 11:45.226
We didn't want it
to become anything.

11:45.269 --> 11:52.320
♪

11:58.761 --> 12:00.589
- What are you doing here?

12:00.632 --> 12:02.634
- Nice to see you too.

12:02.678 --> 12:04.854
I got your text.
You said to pick you up.

12:04.898 --> 12:06.638
- I didn't send a text.

12:06.682 --> 12:09.293
- Well, I didn't
imagine it so...

12:09.337 --> 12:12.296
Why are you so upset?
Am I too close to home?

12:12.340 --> 12:13.776
Are you afraid
what your husband will think?

12:13.820 --> 12:16.518
- Is that why you're here,
to get a reaction?

12:16.561 --> 12:18.650
[soft music]

12:18.694 --> 12:20.696
♪

12:20.740 --> 12:22.872
- Ooh, forgot Theophilus.

12:22.916 --> 12:24.569
Can you bring him from the box?

12:24.613 --> 12:27.137
- Yeah.

12:27.181 --> 12:30.140
[tense music]

12:30.184 --> 12:33.578
- Is this your ancestor?
Dude's ripped.

12:33.622 --> 12:35.406
- [laughs]

12:35.450 --> 12:40.803
♪

12:40.847 --> 12:44.328
O triumphant
and great Theophilus,

12:44.372 --> 12:48.376
My intention to You, My Lord,
is to dedicate myself

12:48.419 --> 12:52.336
onto the sacred path that
You have opened for me.

12:52.380 --> 12:54.338
[long exhale]

12:54.382 --> 12:55.775
[grunts]

12:55.818 --> 12:59.387
[growling]

13:04.566 --> 13:08.788
I surrender to you,
O honorable Lord.

13:14.445 --> 13:15.925
- No, Feej, wait!

13:15.969 --> 13:17.927
[grunts]

13:23.585 --> 13:25.630
- [exhales]

14:13.635 --> 14:16.551
- Are you okay?

14:16.594 --> 14:20.294
Fiji, Fiji.
Your hair.

14:20.337 --> 14:22.905
- You know what I want to do?

14:22.949 --> 14:24.776
- Right--right now?
Are you sure?

14:24.820 --> 14:27.692
- There's only one way to see
if the curse is broken.

14:27.736 --> 14:29.433
[both grunt]

14:29.477 --> 14:32.523
- Kai.

14:32.567 --> 14:35.483
[chuckles]

14:35.526 --> 14:40.009
I'm afraid I have a case
of buyer's remorse.

14:40.053 --> 14:41.924
I want my powers back.

14:41.968 --> 14:44.796
[tense music]

14:44.840 --> 14:47.277
- Look, I'm sorry to say,
but that's why I do

14:47.321 --> 14:49.932
a thorough evaluation before
performing these services,

14:49.976 --> 14:51.586
because the removal
is permanent.

14:51.629 --> 14:53.066
- I understand that
it's bad for business

14:53.109 --> 14:54.806
if word gets out that
you can get refunds,

14:54.850 --> 14:56.547
But I give you my word--
- You're not listening.

14:56.591 --> 14:58.767
There's no going back.
Removing supernatural energy,

14:58.810 --> 15:00.812
it's like dropping
an atom bomb.

15:00.856 --> 15:02.771
Once that energy is released,
it's out there,

15:02.814 --> 15:06.557
so even if I wanted to give
your powers back, I couldn't.

15:06.601 --> 15:09.647
- Olivia, I didn't
get the vial.

15:09.691 --> 15:13.303
Kai lied.
I'm on my way to Manfred.

15:13.347 --> 15:14.783
Okay, bye.

15:14.826 --> 15:17.960
♪

15:18.004 --> 15:20.484
- Hey, Mr. Bridger.
- Are you okay?

15:20.528 --> 15:22.008
- I crashed into
a paving stone,

15:22.051 --> 15:24.488
got thrown off.
Broke my phone.

15:24.532 --> 15:26.447
[scoffs]

15:26.490 --> 15:30.451
- All right,
let's get you cleaned up.

15:30.494 --> 15:32.496
- Ah, thanks.

15:32.540 --> 15:36.370
- I don't get it,
why are you so secretive?

15:36.413 --> 15:38.850
- I'm secretive?
Any time I ask you

15:38.894 --> 15:41.592
a question about your past,
you dodge it.

15:41.636 --> 15:43.464
Why are you doing this?

15:43.507 --> 15:46.119
Why put your life in danger
to hunt demons?

15:53.430 --> 15:57.434
- Can you just do your thing,
please?

15:59.741 --> 16:01.612
- [exhales]

16:01.656 --> 16:03.832
[tense music]

16:03.875 --> 16:07.096
- Stop, stop, no!

16:07.140 --> 16:09.969
- [snarling]
- Help me!

16:10.012 --> 16:13.885
No, please, stop!
No, please!

16:13.929 --> 16:16.976
Stop, stop!

16:17.019 --> 16:18.803
- Mama.

16:18.847 --> 16:20.718
Mama.

16:20.762 --> 16:22.416
- [screams]

16:28.639 --> 16:31.033
- I'm so sorry.

16:34.036 --> 16:36.125
You suffered so much.

16:38.084 --> 16:40.434
- At least
it brought me to you.

16:40.477 --> 16:43.437
[soft music]

16:43.480 --> 16:48.920
♪

16:48.964 --> 16:51.445
[both exhale]

17:01.977 --> 17:03.935
- You can't blame me
for moving on.

17:03.979 --> 17:04.980
You left!

17:05.024 --> 17:07.504
- I didn't do it on a whim!

17:07.548 --> 17:09.463
Why can't you see that
after my own brother

17:09.506 --> 17:10.986
turned out to be
a serial killer

17:11.030 --> 17:12.944
that you chasing me
with a knife was too much?

17:12.988 --> 17:14.990
- I know it was.
It was just hard for me

17:15.034 --> 17:16.644
to accept that I'd lost you,
because that man

17:16.687 --> 17:19.168
chasing you wasn't me.
I was sick.

17:19.212 --> 17:21.127
- You were sick
because you saved Midnight.

17:21.170 --> 17:27.089
I know it's not fair,
but I needed to break free.

17:27.133 --> 17:29.004
I'm sorry I yelled at you.

17:29.048 --> 17:33.095
I'm mostly just mad at myself

17:33.139 --> 17:37.056
because I made this
big, ballsy move to Austin,

17:37.099 --> 17:38.840
and then, the minute
I got your call,

17:38.883 --> 17:41.190
I was just so desperate
for you to miss me

17:41.234 --> 17:45.977
the way that I missed you,
and I just dropped everything.

17:46.021 --> 17:48.980
[soft music]

17:49.024 --> 17:52.636
♪

17:52.680 --> 17:54.160
- I miss you too.

17:54.203 --> 17:56.640
[knock at door]

18:04.126 --> 18:06.650
- Oh.

18:06.694 --> 18:08.739
- Are you okay?
What happened?

18:08.783 --> 18:10.828
- I can come back
at a better time.

18:10.872 --> 18:13.179
- No, uh...

18:15.224 --> 18:18.184
You look upset.
Come in.

18:22.884 --> 18:25.626
- Um...

18:25.669 --> 18:27.889
Kai...

18:27.932 --> 18:29.847
knows about us.

18:29.891 --> 18:31.284
- What?

18:31.327 --> 18:34.243
How?
- He had this voicemail.

18:34.287 --> 18:36.854
It was meant to be
from me to you.

18:36.898 --> 18:39.683
It was uncanny how much
it sounded like me,

18:39.727 --> 18:42.860
but it wasn't me.
I never left that message.

18:42.904 --> 18:44.862
- Two fake voicemails,

18:44.906 --> 18:46.864
both to people
who'd be hurt by us.

18:46.908 --> 18:48.866
It can't be a coincidence.
- Not in Midnight.

18:48.910 --> 18:52.740
- There was another voicemail?
- It's why I came back.

18:52.783 --> 18:55.177
I got this frantic message
from Manfred.

18:55.221 --> 18:57.048
- But I never called her.

18:57.092 --> 19:00.095
Whatever this is,
it's bound to get worse.

19:00.139 --> 19:02.750
And you being a piece
in this puzzle scares me.

19:02.793 --> 19:05.709
- Me too.
- Let's get you out of here.

19:07.711 --> 19:09.713
- I knew I shouldn't
have come back.

19:09.757 --> 19:13.630
- Don't worry,
we'll be out of town soon.

19:13.674 --> 19:15.719
- Okay.

19:18.287 --> 19:20.028
How did we get turned around?

19:20.071 --> 19:21.856
We've been going
in a straight line.

19:21.899 --> 19:24.989
- I don't know, maybe some kids
messed with the sign?

19:25.033 --> 19:27.209
[exhales]

19:27.253 --> 19:31.257
♪

19:31.300 --> 19:33.998
- [breathing heavily]

19:37.263 --> 19:39.178
- We're going back
to town again.

19:39.221 --> 19:42.093
- [breathing heavily]

19:42.137 --> 19:44.313
- Turn around.

19:44.357 --> 19:46.272
[tires screeching]

19:56.717 --> 20:00.024
- We can't leave.
We're trapped.

20:09.556 --> 20:09.773
.

20:09.817 --> 20:12.646
- Mom, I put gas in it.
I'm not lying.

20:12.689 --> 20:16.693
Why--why are you yelling?
Why are you yelling at me--

20:16.737 --> 20:20.480
- Lady, you're kid's doing the
best he can slinging pizzas.

20:20.523 --> 20:22.612
When I was his age,
I was gun-for-hire.

20:22.656 --> 20:25.267
So quit your bitching,
and come get your kid.

20:25.311 --> 20:27.530
Thanks.

20:27.574 --> 20:31.882
- Manfred's still not home,
and my phone's acting up.

20:33.493 --> 20:35.408
[line ringing]

20:35.451 --> 20:37.627
[phone beeping]

20:37.671 --> 20:40.413
- It was just working.

20:40.456 --> 20:42.589
I was just using it.

20:42.632 --> 20:43.720
[line ringing]

20:43.764 --> 20:45.766
[phone beeping]

20:45.809 --> 20:48.769
[lights crackle]

20:48.812 --> 20:52.555
And I'm sure
that's totally unrelated.

20:55.732 --> 20:58.692
- What's wrong?

20:58.735 --> 21:01.782
- I just cheated on my partner
of a thousand years.

21:01.825 --> 21:05.438
That's what's wrong.
What kind of angel am I?

21:05.481 --> 21:07.527
Leaving the fold,
I did that for love.

21:07.570 --> 21:09.790
But this is a darker fall.

21:09.833 --> 21:12.619
The kingdom of Heaven's
never felt so far away.

21:12.662 --> 21:14.447
And for what?

21:14.490 --> 21:19.321
- You may be confused,
but I felt love.

21:20.670 --> 21:22.455
- [exhales]

21:24.761 --> 21:26.589
I'm sorry.

21:30.289 --> 21:33.248
[tense music]

21:33.292 --> 21:35.468
♪

21:35.511 --> 21:38.471
- [moaning]

21:38.514 --> 21:41.300
- Oh, I think the curse
is broken.

21:41.343 --> 21:43.345
Otherwise, I would have died
a thousand deaths

21:43.389 --> 21:44.825
after what we just did.

21:44.868 --> 21:46.696
[both exhale]

21:52.006 --> 21:54.487
[light clicking repeatedly]

21:57.664 --> 21:59.492
Weird.

22:03.757 --> 22:06.716
[tense music]

22:06.760 --> 22:11.808
♪

22:11.852 --> 22:13.897
Hey, the power's out.

22:13.941 --> 22:16.509
We should go check on everyone.

22:16.552 --> 22:18.598
- Knock yourself out.

22:21.383 --> 22:23.385
- You okay?

22:23.429 --> 22:25.953
- I just
carved a hole in my chest.

22:25.996 --> 22:29.913
If it ain't a bellini
and a bath, I ain't down.

22:33.961 --> 22:36.442
- You're right.

22:36.485 --> 22:38.661
You've had a big night.
- Mm-hmm.

22:38.705 --> 22:40.663
I'll be back as soon as I can.

22:40.707 --> 22:43.492
[both moan]

22:43.536 --> 22:45.755
- [breathing heavily]

22:45.799 --> 22:48.497
- I love you.

22:48.541 --> 22:50.412
- I know.

22:55.939 --> 22:58.420
- I don't know
another way to describe it.

22:58.464 --> 23:01.641
A magic loop
is keeping us stuck in town.

23:01.684 --> 23:03.425
- Well, maybe it's a spell
or an illusion

23:03.469 --> 23:04.470
that's making people
think that.

23:04.513 --> 23:05.775
- But it's not just the loop.

23:05.819 --> 23:07.560
There's no cell service.
It's a blackout.

23:07.603 --> 23:11.390
- And fake voicemails.
Someone's screwing with us.

23:11.433 --> 23:12.956
You look decidedly human.

23:13.000 --> 23:14.915
Kai refuse
to give your power back?

23:14.958 --> 23:17.570
- He lied, said they
couldn't be recycled.

23:17.613 --> 23:19.833
Then he got angry.
- Not surprised.

23:19.876 --> 23:22.488
I'm telling you,
he's behind all this.

23:22.531 --> 23:23.793
He's got a stockpile
of monster powers.

23:23.837 --> 23:25.578
He could pull off
a lot of tricks.

23:25.621 --> 23:27.841
- Well, we need to get in there
and get your power back.

23:27.884 --> 23:31.410
- Yes, and Kai draws his power
from that creepy-ass head.

23:31.453 --> 23:33.716
That's his Achilles'.
So I'm thinking--

23:33.760 --> 23:36.719
- He took our powers.
Let's take his.

23:36.763 --> 23:39.722
[tense music]

23:39.766 --> 23:42.943
♪

23:42.986 --> 23:47.469
- That's Kai's office.
That's where the head is.

23:47.513 --> 23:49.340
I'll need those angel hands
of yours.

23:49.384 --> 23:52.082
Last time I touched it, it
kind of knocked me on my ass.

23:56.478 --> 23:57.784
Who's down for a break-in?

23:57.827 --> 23:59.873
- I'm down.
- Always.

24:03.659 --> 24:05.313
- [in Joe's voice]
Walker, it's me.

24:05.356 --> 24:08.708
I am sorry about earlier,
but I need your help.

24:08.751 --> 24:11.058
There's a demon in Midnight.

24:13.626 --> 24:16.455
[in normal voice]
Sayonara, Chuy.

24:21.068 --> 24:22.112
- Where'd you get
a Rubik's Cube

24:22.156 --> 24:23.679
that messes with people?

24:23.723 --> 24:26.334
- Would you believe me
if I said Amazon?

24:26.377 --> 24:28.510
I just love games, don't you?

24:28.554 --> 24:30.947
- I saw what you did
from my porch,

24:30.991 --> 24:32.993
the little light trick
in Kai's office.

24:33.036 --> 24:35.691
- Oh, yeah.
- Who are you?

24:35.735 --> 24:37.867
- Basil.

24:37.911 --> 24:40.740
- What are you?
- I'm a demigod,

24:40.783 --> 24:43.394
a trickster, to be exact.
I get into human business,

24:43.438 --> 24:45.571
stir the pot,
create some chaos.

24:45.614 --> 24:48.530
- Like in
Native American folklore.

24:48.574 --> 24:50.010
Tricksters
were kind of lovable.

24:50.053 --> 24:52.360
- Yeah, because
they never met me.

24:52.403 --> 24:56.799
No, I'm a big, fat sadist.
Emotional suffering is my jam.

24:56.843 --> 24:59.846
I know people's secrets,
perks of being omniscient.

24:59.889 --> 25:03.806
Title of my autobiography:
"Secrets That Ruin Lives."

25:03.850 --> 25:05.852
Let's say I send a message

25:05.895 --> 25:08.681
to this guy's ex-girlfriend,
luring her back to town.

25:08.724 --> 25:11.597
Thanks to my knack for timing,
she shows up at his door

25:11.640 --> 25:14.513
just in time to see him
macking on a married chick.

25:14.556 --> 25:18.778
I tinker. I toss bread crumbs.
Secrets become known.

25:18.821 --> 25:20.823
Humans are exposed
for the gluttonous,

25:20.867 --> 25:24.740
sex-crazed monster babies
that they are, and voilà:

25:24.784 --> 25:26.916
friends and lovers
start killing each other.

25:26.960 --> 25:29.440
- So, basically,
you're a reality show producer.

25:29.484 --> 25:31.051
[both laugh]

25:31.094 --> 25:32.879
Why come to a little town
like Midnight?

25:32.922 --> 25:35.795
- Because of the energy, duh.

25:35.838 --> 25:38.580
I love the shock
on people's faces

25:38.624 --> 25:40.887
when they realize that
I'm the puppet master

25:40.930 --> 25:42.976
and they're my pawns,
my little playthings.

25:43.019 --> 25:45.195
- And what makes you think
I won't tell your playthings

25:45.239 --> 25:47.589
what you've been up to?

25:47.633 --> 25:49.025
- Because you stopped
giving a damn

25:49.069 --> 25:50.984
about these people an hour ago.

25:51.027 --> 25:54.074
[dramatic music]

25:57.991 --> 25:58.208
.

25:58.252 --> 26:01.081
[tense music]

26:01.124 --> 26:06.216
♪

26:06.260 --> 26:10.612
- I know you don't believe me,
but I'm going to find a way

26:10.656 --> 26:14.224
to prove to you that
that message wasn't from me.

26:17.140 --> 26:19.621
- [groaning]

26:19.665 --> 26:21.318
Hey, I'm really sorry
to bother you,

26:21.362 --> 26:24.234
but I felt a tear
in my back.

26:24.278 --> 26:26.585
Can you do
some of your woo-woo?

26:26.628 --> 26:28.499
- Look, maybe when the
power's back. Right now--

26:28.543 --> 26:30.197
- Oh, please, man.
I'm desperate, I'm desperate.

26:30.240 --> 26:32.286
- Okay, okay.

26:32.329 --> 26:34.070
Come on.
- Ooh!

26:34.114 --> 26:36.420
[groaning]

26:36.464 --> 26:38.161
- Hi, I'm sorry.

26:38.205 --> 26:41.077
I thought that you left town
with Manfred.

26:42.688 --> 26:45.647
- Could I talk to you
in private?

26:45.691 --> 26:47.693
- All right.

26:47.736 --> 26:50.304
- Great, thanks.

26:50.347 --> 26:53.307
[tense music]

26:53.350 --> 26:56.353
♪

26:56.397 --> 26:59.618
- Meet back at the pawn shop?
- Yeah.

27:16.547 --> 27:18.637
- It's in there.

27:24.338 --> 27:26.993
Careful.

27:39.005 --> 27:41.355
- [grunts]

27:42.443 --> 27:45.141
- You okay?
- Yeah.

27:45.185 --> 27:46.708
That's not happening.

27:46.752 --> 27:49.145
Whatever spell's on this thing,
it's tethered here.

27:49.189 --> 27:51.365
- Maybe it's like
King Arthur's sword.

27:51.408 --> 27:53.280
Only Kai can move it.

27:55.021 --> 27:58.067
[phone chimes]

28:00.591 --> 28:02.376
- Joe, I'm going to surveil
the diner for that demon.

28:02.419 --> 28:04.334
Where are you?

28:15.389 --> 28:18.392
[indistinct chatter]

28:38.586 --> 28:40.631
- Watch this.

28:56.517 --> 28:59.172
- I'm still protective
of Manfred,

28:59.215 --> 29:01.391
and given your situation,

29:01.435 --> 29:04.786
you should know that he doesn't
deserve to be messed with.

29:04.830 --> 29:07.658
- Well, I'm not
messing with him.

29:07.702 --> 29:11.488
He's--he's one
of my greatest joys.

29:11.532 --> 29:14.230
I really do
care about him very much.

29:14.274 --> 29:17.843
- But do you love him?
Because I do.

29:19.758 --> 29:21.237
- Are you two thinking
about getting--

29:21.281 --> 29:22.499
[knock at door]

29:22.543 --> 29:24.501
Come in.

29:28.592 --> 29:29.811
I'm sorry,
I need to excuse myself.

29:29.855 --> 29:31.857
- Oh, um, why don't
I come with you?

29:31.900 --> 29:33.380
- No, no, no,
it's an emergency.

29:33.423 --> 29:35.208
I have to go.

29:35.251 --> 29:38.211
[tense music]

29:38.254 --> 29:43.782
♪

29:43.825 --> 29:45.566
[phone chimes]

29:56.446 --> 29:59.101
- The jukebox
should be right here.

29:59.145 --> 30:00.668
- They must have moved it
to hide the vials.

30:00.711 --> 30:02.322
- [scoffs]

30:08.371 --> 30:09.851
- What are you doing here?

30:11.679 --> 30:13.637
[gasps]

30:13.681 --> 30:15.857
- He wants his powers back.

30:17.903 --> 30:22.429
- The writing carved into the
skin, it's definitely Syriac.

30:22.472 --> 30:24.213
- The guy really
pissed somebody off.

30:24.257 --> 30:26.433
- Yeah.
- Can you translate?

30:26.476 --> 30:29.175
- Syriac's ancient.
I'm a bit rusty.

30:29.218 --> 30:31.220
But I have some reference books
back at the pawn shop.

30:31.264 --> 30:34.223
[tense music]

30:34.267 --> 30:36.269
♪

30:36.312 --> 30:38.314
Got it, let's go.
- Wait.

30:38.358 --> 30:40.360
Let me try something first.

30:51.371 --> 30:54.374
[dramatic music]

30:58.900 --> 30:59.074
.

30:59.118 --> 31:01.947
[tense music]

31:01.990 --> 31:09.041
♪

31:29.235 --> 31:31.367
- Manfred?

31:35.023 --> 31:37.678
[dramatic music]

31:37.721 --> 31:40.159
- Why would Manfred
be in my office?

31:40.202 --> 31:41.987
♪

31:42.030 --> 31:44.337
- I know you have ancestor
body parts, but mm-mm, man,

31:44.380 --> 31:46.861
that sounds next level.
No, thank you.

31:46.905 --> 31:48.428
Hey.

31:48.471 --> 31:50.169
- Looks like
you're short a head.

31:50.212 --> 31:52.998
- Yeah, yeah.
How'd you guys do?

31:53.041 --> 31:56.001
[tense music]

31:56.044 --> 32:00.135
♪

32:00.179 --> 32:03.225
- Oh, that's what
I'm talking about.

32:03.269 --> 32:06.881
Oh, hell yes!

32:06.925 --> 32:08.404
Welcome back.

32:08.448 --> 32:09.971
- I never thought
I'd be so happy

32:10.015 --> 32:12.234
to see those
big blue eyes again.

32:12.278 --> 32:15.368
- Our disembodied head,
it's alive.

32:15.411 --> 32:17.370
- Oh, joy.

32:17.413 --> 32:20.460
Well, FYI,
someone moved the jukebox.

32:20.503 --> 32:22.288
- But Patience
got us the vial.

32:22.331 --> 32:24.420
I don't know where that
leaves her when Kai finds out.

32:24.464 --> 32:26.031
- Creek was supposed
to be on Patience.

32:26.074 --> 32:28.337
Where's Creek?

32:28.381 --> 32:30.949
I'm going into the hotel.

32:30.992 --> 32:32.994
- We'll go with you.

32:33.038 --> 32:34.822
[tense music]

32:34.865 --> 32:37.390
[indistinct chatter]

32:37.433 --> 32:44.440
♪

32:47.487 --> 32:49.532
- Joe, look out!
He's a demon!

32:49.576 --> 32:51.186
- Stop!

32:52.883 --> 32:54.233
He's my husband.

32:56.017 --> 32:58.237
- Who the hell is this?

32:58.280 --> 33:01.980
- This is Walker.
We hunt together.

33:11.467 --> 33:13.034
- [distorted voice]
I can't imagine why

33:13.078 --> 33:14.383
you wouldn't want me
to know about him.

33:14.427 --> 33:17.256
- Take it easy, Chuy.

33:17.299 --> 33:19.127
Calm down.

33:19.171 --> 33:23.436
Chuy, come on, breathe.

33:23.479 --> 33:25.525
- Hey, everyone,
get inside.

33:25.568 --> 33:27.440
It is not safe out here.
Lock the door.

33:27.483 --> 33:30.486
Get inside, come on, come on.
- Just look at me.

33:30.530 --> 33:33.011
Just breathe.
Look at me.

33:35.839 --> 33:38.103
- What the hell?
- Give me a minute.

33:38.146 --> 33:40.279
[breathing heavily]

33:40.322 --> 33:42.411
- Oh, God,
this martini is everything.

33:42.455 --> 33:47.329
- Finally, banging a
bartender's good for something.

33:47.373 --> 33:49.201
- I thought you were home.
- No.

33:49.244 --> 33:51.986
- We got to get inside.
Chuy might blow a fuse.

33:52.030 --> 33:54.423
- Well, I can
take care of myself.

33:54.467 --> 33:57.165
- No, I know you can,
but it's safer inside.

33:57.209 --> 33:59.820
[yells]

33:59.863 --> 34:02.214
You burned me!
- You spilled my drink.

34:02.257 --> 34:03.476
- Your drink?

34:03.519 --> 34:05.260
This is what
I was worried about.

34:05.304 --> 34:07.306
It's that Dark Witch stuff.

34:07.349 --> 34:09.090
You're not you anymore.

34:09.134 --> 34:13.181
- Oh, honey, I'm more me
than I've ever been.

34:13.225 --> 34:16.184
[tense music]

34:16.228 --> 34:19.492
♪

34:19.535 --> 34:21.363
- [groans]

34:24.366 --> 34:25.585
- If you could look inside me,

34:25.628 --> 34:27.456
see what I saw,
feel what I felt

34:27.500 --> 34:30.416
and still hide this from me,
it's no wonder your fallen.

34:30.459 --> 34:33.245
- You don't belong with God.

34:33.288 --> 34:37.292
- I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to hurt you.

34:41.383 --> 34:44.082
- You weren't just
hunting together, were you?

34:45.953 --> 34:49.565
[growls]

34:49.609 --> 34:51.306
- Chuy, Chuy, no!

34:51.350 --> 34:52.873
[grunting]

34:52.916 --> 34:55.354
[dramatic music]

34:55.397 --> 34:59.097
- [screaming]

35:00.402 --> 35:02.578
[roars and screaming]

35:13.720 --> 35:16.984
- [roars]

35:17.027 --> 35:19.987
- Stop!

35:20.030 --> 35:22.076
Enough!

35:22.120 --> 35:23.425
- Creek?

35:27.734 --> 35:31.085
- You're looking for Creek?
I was just looking for Kai.

35:31.129 --> 35:33.609
[distant scream]

35:33.653 --> 35:36.177
- Get in that room,
lock the door.

35:36.221 --> 35:37.483
I'll come for you
when it's safe.

35:37.526 --> 35:38.571
- All right.

35:38.614 --> 35:40.225
- [growling]

35:40.268 --> 35:43.402
- Please, Chuy, we can
come back from this.

35:43.445 --> 35:45.969
Please come back to me.

35:54.674 --> 35:56.719
- [roars]

36:04.423 --> 36:04.640
.

36:04.684 --> 36:06.120
- [roaring]

36:06.164 --> 36:08.166
[grunts]

36:08.209 --> 36:11.169
[dramatic music]

36:11.212 --> 36:15.042
♪

36:15.085 --> 36:18.088
- No, no, no, no, no!
You're letting him go!

36:18.132 --> 36:20.700
- Stay out of this.
- Why are you letting him go?

36:20.743 --> 36:23.398
- I can talk him down.
- Look around you.

36:23.442 --> 36:24.704
If we hadn't been here,

36:24.747 --> 36:26.445
this would have been
a massacre!

36:26.488 --> 36:29.535
People could die, all right?
He needs be put down.

36:29.578 --> 36:32.015
♪

36:32.059 --> 36:33.930
- Go find your husband.

36:37.673 --> 36:39.458
[exhales]

36:43.984 --> 36:47.466
- Hey, hey, everyone,
I'm so sorry.

36:47.509 --> 36:50.120
- What--what the hell
is wrong with you people?

36:50.164 --> 36:52.384
We came to Midnight
to realize our dreams,

36:52.427 --> 36:55.430
and it's been
one nightmare after another.

36:55.474 --> 36:57.432
And you,

36:57.476 --> 36:58.912
how would you feel
if I reached into your life

36:58.955 --> 37:00.218
and snuffed out
everything you love?

37:00.261 --> 37:02.132
- Kai, Kai.
- No, no, no.

37:02.176 --> 37:04.744
Get out!
All of you, get out!

37:04.787 --> 37:06.615
And never step foot
in here again.

37:06.659 --> 37:08.704
And you, you stay the hell away
from my wife!

37:08.748 --> 37:10.793
- All right, come on, Kai.

37:10.837 --> 37:12.926
[tense music]

37:12.969 --> 37:15.015
I'm sorry.

37:15.058 --> 37:17.626
[clapping]

37:19.237 --> 37:21.064
- Mwah, bravo, Midnight!

37:21.108 --> 37:22.849
[laughs]

37:22.892 --> 37:25.939
I haven't had this much fun
since the Donner party.

37:25.982 --> 37:27.245
Doesn't include you guys.

37:27.288 --> 37:29.029
You gave me
nothing to play with.

37:29.072 --> 37:33.773
- Wait, wait, wait!
- No, no, no, no, no.

37:33.816 --> 37:37.211
You were my favorite toy.

37:37.255 --> 37:40.823
Oh, your life
is a dumpster fire.

37:40.867 --> 37:42.477
Thank you.

37:42.521 --> 37:44.218
♪

37:44.262 --> 37:46.786
And this handsome man-peach!

37:46.829 --> 37:48.701
Oh, hey, hey!

37:51.573 --> 37:54.489
You are so damaged.

37:54.533 --> 37:56.578
Never change.

38:00.887 --> 38:03.498
Oh, Midnight, I wish
I could stay and chat,

38:03.542 --> 38:05.544
but I got
a congressional hearing

38:05.587 --> 38:07.154
I got to skip off to.

38:07.197 --> 38:11.114
Hey, let's do this again,
shall we?

38:17.120 --> 38:19.558
- Yo, what the hell
just happened?

38:19.601 --> 38:21.647
- My life's a dumpster fire?

38:21.690 --> 38:24.606
- And, Lem,
why did you stop me?

38:24.650 --> 38:26.173
- It hit me.

38:26.216 --> 38:30.090
He's a trickster, a demigod.
You can't kill him.

38:30.133 --> 38:33.485
They manipulate
and kill for sport.

38:33.528 --> 38:35.878
I crossed paths with one during
the Mexican-American War,

38:35.922 --> 38:38.098
and I hoped
I never would again.

38:38.141 --> 38:40.056
- How do we make sure
he never comes back?

38:40.100 --> 38:42.711
- We don't give him
a reason to come back.

38:42.755 --> 38:45.323
Tricksters feed off turmoil.

38:45.366 --> 38:47.673
That's why
he was bored with us.

38:47.716 --> 38:50.545
We have no secrets.

38:50.589 --> 38:53.287
If we don't want him
to come back,

38:53.331 --> 38:57.726
we live our lives cards up
with love for each other.

38:57.770 --> 39:00.729
[tense music]

39:00.773 --> 39:07.823
♪

39:12.741 --> 39:14.308
- Y'all going
to keep me prisoner?

39:14.352 --> 39:16.876
- I'd prefer
we come to an agreement,

39:16.919 --> 39:20.358
that you let Joe
take care of Chuy.

39:20.401 --> 39:22.621
- Agreed.

39:25.363 --> 39:27.103
- Did you check the basement?
- Everywhere.

39:27.147 --> 39:29.367
I'm telling you,
we swept the entire hotel,

39:29.410 --> 39:31.325
nothing.
- Maybe she got out before us.

39:31.369 --> 39:35.155
- Hey, is everyone okay?
- Have you seen Creek?

39:35.198 --> 39:37.592
- Yeah, yeah, she took off
in her car.

39:37.636 --> 39:39.638
- No, she wouldn't just leave.

39:39.681 --> 39:42.118
- Well, why not?
She did before.

39:42.162 --> 39:43.381
- [scoffs]

39:43.424 --> 39:45.861
- It's self-preservation.

39:45.905 --> 39:48.821
Midnight is nothing
but bad memories for her.

39:48.864 --> 39:51.737
- There's more to it than that.

39:51.780 --> 39:56.132
You know what Lem said
about not keeping secrets?

39:56.176 --> 39:58.918
He's right.

39:58.961 --> 40:02.965
I've been having an affair
with Patience, and Creek saw.

40:04.793 --> 40:08.101
- Man.
- That's--oh--

40:08.144 --> 40:09.711
okay.

40:09.755 --> 40:12.714
[tense music]

40:12.758 --> 40:14.760
♪

40:14.803 --> 40:20.983
- Bobo, I'm so sorry.
I was horrible.

40:21.027 --> 40:24.030
It was the Dark Magic.
You were right.

40:24.073 --> 40:26.424
I was just struggling
to harness it.

40:26.467 --> 40:29.209
It's so new to me.

40:31.037 --> 40:33.343
Oh.

40:33.387 --> 40:36.346
[soft music]

40:36.390 --> 40:38.261
Please forgive me.

40:38.305 --> 40:45.355
♪

40:50.273 --> 40:53.363
- ♪ Caught in the riptide

40:57.019 --> 41:00.283
♪ I was searching
for the truth ♪

41:05.027 --> 41:08.988
♪ There was a reason

41:09.031 --> 41:11.730
[phone clicking]

41:11.773 --> 41:13.209
♪ I collided into you

41:13.253 --> 41:15.777
[line ringing]

41:15.821 --> 41:18.867
- Hi, you've reached Creek.
Leave me a message.

41:18.911 --> 41:22.305
- Creek, listen.

41:22.349 --> 41:25.483
I--I know I'm to blame
for you leaving,

41:25.526 --> 41:29.356
so I'm sorry.

41:29.399 --> 41:33.969
But just--just let me know
when you're home.

41:34.013 --> 41:36.058
I love you.

41:41.455 --> 41:43.457
- Manfred?

41:43.501 --> 41:45.503
- [scoffs]

41:48.418 --> 41:51.378
[dramatic music]

41:51.421 --> 41:53.293
No!

41:53.336 --> 41:55.730
- I love you too.
- No!

41:55.774 --> 41:57.079
- I'm so sorry.

41:57.123 --> 42:00.169
- Who did this to you?

42:00.213 --> 42:07.263
♪
